Subject: Crowd- & Alternatively Funding Your Career
Description: Our panelists discuss their experiences using entrepreneurship opportunities like Startup Weekend and Global Startup Battle or crowdfunding platforms like Kickstarter and Patreon, to supplement or make a living, or start a new project.  Speakers include:Tanya DePass, Mark Oshiro, Christina York, Noa Page - Track: Life  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: Flash Comics!
Description: No we're not talking about the fastest man alive, we're talking about the wild new form of comics that incorporate the technology of today! These comics keep you on the edge of your seat and pull you in even deeper with stunning animations interwoven into the frames! Just when you thought you knew comics!  Speakers include:Noa Page - Track: Comics  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: Intro to Comics
Description: We've all grown up around comics, watched tons of movie adaptations of them, and gathered around the television on Saturday mornings to watch cartoons based on them ...right? Well in case you didn't, this panel is for you! Learn about comics media and why it's so great! An intro for the uninitiated!   Speakers include:Noa Page, BluRaven C. Houvener, Jon David - Track: Comics  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none
